This paper deals with the welfare aspects of random assignment mechanisms, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the properties of these mechanisms, such as truthfulness and envy-freeness, which are important in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve analyzing different classes of utility functions and distributions, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing the efficiency of different mechanisms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and social networks (cs.SI).
